        <!-- Section 1: Overview -->
        <section id="overview" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-amber-400 mb-4 border-b border-amber-700 pb-2">Module I: The Path of the Inoculated</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-400 mb-8">
                This section provides the high-level summary for this adventure module. Use this to establish the setting, objectives, and core conflict for your Logicians (players) as they prepare to cure the Miasma of Unreason.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-xl shadow-2xl p-6 border border-amber-600/50">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-500 mb-4">Module Details</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone-300">
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-amber-200">Objective:</strong> The Miasma of Unreason has contaminated the population, targeting belief in the **Axiom Serum** (The Vaccine). Logicians must travel the path, defeat the core Fallacy Encounters, and restore the **Mantra of Evidence** to the populace.</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-amber-200">Adversary Focus:</strong> Misinformation and Fear (Black/Red/White/Blue/Hybrid)</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-amber-200">Recommended Level:</strong> Initiate (Designed for 1-2 Logicians)</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-6 border-zinc-700">

                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-500 mb-4">The Blight of Unreason</h3>
                <p class="text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
                    The current Blight is swift, but the Axiom Serum, properly administered, offers near-total protection. Yet, an unprecedented wave of intellectual corruption has stalled its acceptance. The Logician's quest is not to heal the body, but to cure the infected mind.
                </p>
                <p class="text-stone-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                    The primary vectors of the Miasma are known as the **Doubt Speakers**—corrupted individuals who have traded factual conviction for popular, ruinous narratives.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Encounter 1 -->
        <section id="encounter-1" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-amber-400 mb-4 border-b border-amber-700 pb-2">Encounter 1: The Bazaar of Half-Truths</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-400 mb-6">
                Your Logicians enter the bustling city center, where a crowd buzzes with rumors. This encounter tests their ability to counter popular opinion and disarm diversionary tactics from the Rumor Merchant.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-xl shadow-xl p-6 border border-zinc-700 mb-6">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Location</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">The bustling, crowded heart of the outer city. The crowd is agitated, murmuring rumors that grow louder with every passing moment.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Adversary</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">**The Rumor Merchant** (The embodiment of popular, unverified claims).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4">Fallacy Card Duels</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4 accordion-container">
                <!-- Accordion Item 1 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Bandwagon
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-w">W</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Initial Defense.** The Rumor Merchant’s first move. “Everyone in the Bazaar doubts the Serum! Join the crowd, Logician. You alone cannot be right against so many voices.” This must be countered by asserting the non-validity of consensus over evidence.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 2 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Red Herring
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-r">R</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Diversion.** When the Logician tries to present evidence of the Serum's efficacy, the Merchant counters by flashing a crimson light: "Did you hear the Citadel is raising taxes? That's the real threat!" This forces the player to expend a counter-spell to regain focus on the central argument.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 3 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Ad Hominem
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-r">R</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Final Attack.** If the Rumor Merchant is cornered by irrefutable data, they strike at the source: "You’re just a pawn of the Citadel's high-and-mighty academics! Why should we trust a bookish fool like you?" Players must defeat this by proving that the *source* is irrelevant to the *evidence*.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 bg-green-900/50 border-l-4 border-green-500 text-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <strong class="font-bold">Victory Condition:</strong> All three fallacies are shattered, and the Rumor Merchant is forced to retract their statement publicly. The crowd begins to disperse, showing faint signs of reason.
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3: Encounter 2 -->
        <section id="encounter-2" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-amber-400 mb-4 border-b border-amber-700 pb-2">Encounter 2: The Chamber of Twisted Data</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-400 mb-6">
                The Logicians now enter a place of knowledge, corrupted. The Archivist Scrivener, a fallen Logician, uses data itself to create confusion. This encounter tests the ability to demand context, expose statistical flaws, and defy emotional manipulation.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-xl shadow-xl p-6 border border-zinc-700 mb-6">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Location</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">A ruined section of the City Archives, filled with disorganized scrolls and broken data tablets.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Adversary</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">**Archivist Scrivener** (A corrupted Logician who manipulates data points).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4">Fallacy Card Duels</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4 accordion-container">
                <!-- Accordion Item 1 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Cherry-Picking
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-b">B</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Opening Lie.** The Scrivener isolates a single, dark scroll detailing one adverse event from the entire clinical trial. "See this rotten cherry? The trial failed! All other positive reports are irrelevant." The player must invoke the **Context Spell** to reveal the whole data set.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 2 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Anecdotal Evidence
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-b">B</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Personal Focus.** The Scrivener shifts focus from statistics to a vivid, emotional story: "My own brother's neighbor felt ill! Do not trust your charts; trust the pain of a single, vivid tale!" This isolates the player’s mind from statistical defense.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 3 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Post Hoc (False Cause)
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="2">2</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-r">R</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Causal Trap.** When faced with the timeline, the Scrivener lays the trap: "The Serum was administered, and then the fever returned. That which follows must be caused by the preceding event!" The player must counter by revealing confounding variables and the natural coincidence of events.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 4 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Base Rate Fallacy
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="2">2</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-b">B</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Final Confusion.** The Scrivener uses numbers to create confusion: "Of all the new fever cases, the majority were among those who took the Serum! Therefore, the Serum *causes* the fever!" The Logician must counter by proving the denominator—that the vaccinated population is so large the majority of *any* event is expected to occur among them, but at a lower *risk* than the unvaccinated.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 bg-green-900/50 border-l-4 border-green-500 text-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <strong class="font-bold">Victory Condition:</strong> The Archival records are reorganized and the correct context is restored to the data.
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4: Encounter 3 -->
        <section id="encounter-3" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-amber-400 mb-4 border-b border-amber-700 pb-2">Encounter 3: The Peak of Panic</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-400 mb-6">
                This is the final confrontation. At the Spires of Certainty, the Prophet of Doubt uses pure emotional power, exaggeration, and ideological traps. Logicians must hold fast to logic in the face of manufactured terror and impossible standards.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-xl shadow-xl p-6 border border-zinc-700 mb-6">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Location</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">The final climb toward the highest point in the city, the Spires of Certainty. The air is thin, and the shadows are highly effective.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">Adversary</h4>
                        <p class="text-stone-300">**The Prophet of Doubt** (The master of emotional argument and exaggeration).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4">Fallacy Card Duels</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4 accordion-container">
                <!-- Accordion Item 1 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Slippery Slope
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="2">2</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-u">U</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Descent.** The Prophet conjures a vision: "If we accept the Serum, next they will monitor our every move, then control our thoughts, and finally, enslave the land! Reject the first step!" This must be defeated by exposing the lack of inevitable links in the chain.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 2 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Appeal to Fear
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-cost-hybrid mana-rb">R/B</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Terror Strike.** A sudden wave of intense anxiety washes over the Logician: "The side effects! The theoretical dangers! Can you live with that unknown? Be afraid, Logician!" The player must invoke the **Risk Assessment Spell** to compare the theoretical danger to the known danger of the disease.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 3 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Perfectionist Fallacy
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="2">2</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-u">U</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Impossible Standard.** The Prophet strikes a righteous pose: "The Serum is only 90% effective! If it is not perfect and absolute, it is a failure and should be dismissed entirely!" The Logician must defeat this by proving that *better is the enemy of perfect* and defending the value of incremental improvement.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 4 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            False Dichotomy
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-cost-hybrid mana-bw">B/W</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**The Corner.** The Prophet forces the final choice: "You must either accept the Serum is pure poison, or accept the Citadel controls your will! There is no middle ground, Logician!" The player must reveal the third, hidden path: **Informed Choice Based on Reviewed Evidence.**</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Item 5 -->
                <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-zinc-700 overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left font-semibold text-lg text-stone-200 hover:bg-zinc-700">
                        <span class="flex items-center">
                            Toxin Fallacy
                            <span class="mana-cost mana-cost-hybrid mana-gu">G/U</span>
                            <span class="mana-cost" data-cost="1">1</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="accordion-arrow text-amber-500 text-2xl">↓</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content px-5 pb-5">
                        <p class="text-stone-300 italic">**Final Gambit.** As the Prophet is defeated, they whisper one last charm: "Look closer at the contents—Formaldehyde! It is poison! It is death!" This last, desperate charm must be defeated by invoking the science of **Dose-Response** and the body’s natural chemistry.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 bg-green-900/50 border-l-4 border-green-500 text-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <strong class="font-bold">Victory Condition:</strong> The Prophet of Doubt is silenced, the Miasma is cleansed from the Spires, and the Mantra of Evidence is broadcast across the land.
            </div>
        </section>

